    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#łajtar-abdel-karim2008"/><citedRange/></bibl> and
                    <bibl><ptr target="#cdlBE"/>, <citedRange>2012.504</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>58.1841</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>114600</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2013"/>, pp. <citedRange>186-187</citedRange></bibl>, whence
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>64.2014</citedRange></bibl>;
                <bibl><ptr target="#cdl2013-2014"/>, p. <citedRange>187</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key=""><name nymRef="#Αιαλαν">Αιαλαντος</name></persName>· 
                    <lb n="2"/><w>ἀκίνητος</w>
                </ab></div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
               </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Tombe</supplied> d'Aialan; à ne pas déplacer.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Tomb</supplied> of Aialan; not to be moved.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
                <p><supplied reason="subaudible">Tomba</supplied> di Aialan; non spostare.</p>
            </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>This rare use of the adjective <foreign xml:lang="grc">ἀκίνητος</foreign> is one of the many formulas preventing the tomb to be opened, robbed or
                    re-used. A similar mention is to be found at Amphissa (see <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>56.566</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
                <p/>
            </div></body>
